i","tag-bad-deeds-al-sayyiat","tag-dogs","tag-fiqh","tag-manners-adab","tag-prayer-al-salat","tag-prostration-sujud","tag-laziness-sloth-al-kasl"],"aioseo_notices":[],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"","jetpack_shortlink":"https:\/\/wp.me\/p95VHY-4qN","jetpack_sharing_enabled":true,"jetpack-related-posts":[{"id":33026,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/08\/01\/prophets-dua-ruku-sujud\/","url_meta":{"origin":17037,"position":0},"title":"Hadith on Salat: The Prophet&#8217;s supplication in bowing, prostration","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 1, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, would say in his bowing and prostration, \u201cGlory be to you, Allah our Lord, and your praises. Forgive me.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 4042, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 484 Grade:\u00a0Muttafaqun Alayhi\u00a0(authenticity agreed upon) according to Al-Bukhari and Muslim \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0627\u0626\u0650\u0634\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0636\u0650\u064a\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652\u0647\u064e\u0627\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25464,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/11\/29\/raising-hands-in-salat\/","url_meta":{"origin":17037,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Salat: Description of raising the hands in prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"November 29, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdullah ibn Umar reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, would raise his hands parallel to his shoulders when he entered into prayer, and when he exalted Allah for bowing. When he raised his head from bowing, he would likewise raise his hands and say, \u201cAllah\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":15536,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/08\/01\/two-prostrations-sujud-al-sahwa\/","url_meta":{"origin":17037,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Salah: Satan makes him remember the world in prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 1, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cVerily, if one of you stands for prayer, Satan comes to distract him until he does not know how many cycles he has performed. When that happens to one of you, let him perform two prostrations\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":17357,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/12\/28\/forget-salat-sujud-al-sahwa\/","url_meta":{"origin":17037,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Prayer: When one forgets number of raka&#8217;at in prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 28, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdullah ibn Mas\u2019ud reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, prayed with us five cycles (raka'at). We said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, you added something to the prayer.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201cWhat is that?\u201d They said, \u201cYou have prayed five cycles.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201cVerily, I\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":37572,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/12\/19\/many-sujood\/","url_meta":{"origin":17037,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Sajdah: Prostration raises a degree, erases a sin","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 19, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Thawban reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cYou must perform many prostrations to Allah, for you do not prostrate to Allah but that Allah will raise you one degree for it and erase one sin for it.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 488 Grade: Sahih (authentic)\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":17544,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/01\/09\/nearest-allah-sujud-dua\/","url_meta":{"origin":17037,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Sujud: You are nearest to Allah in prostration","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 9, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cThe servant is closest to his Lord during prostration, so increase your supplications therein.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 482 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Muslim \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0647\u064f\u0631\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0631\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0623\u064e\u0646\u0651\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064e \u06